At the invitation of the Beijing Municipal Government and to further implement people-to-people and cultural exchanges between China and Central and Eastern Europe countries (CEEC) as part of the Belt and Road Initiative, the Bulgarian Embassy in China invited the famous Bulgarian pop jazz singer Ruth Koleva to Beijing to participate in the Beijing Day event and the China-CEEC culture and art carnival at the International Horticultural Exhibition 2019 Beijing organized by the Beijing Municipal Government. Before the event, the Bulgarian Embassy will hold a press conference on Wednesday, introducing Koleva and her activities during her visit in Beijing. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun